            "heading": "(Core 2 / Spark only)"
          }
        },
        "subheading_4FUbLa": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Tracking on Core / Spark"
          }
        },
        "text_TLzjQj": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>In the <strong>Track</strong> app, set the duration of your practice session and select the instrument you will be using.</p><p>To modify the list of instruments available on your device, open the mobile app and navigate to:</p><p><strong>Settings → User Profile → Instruments</strong></p><p>To begin your session, tap the soundwave icon twice quickly.</p>"
          }
        },
        "image_FfyzYr": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Core_2_Order_12.jpg"
          }
        },
        "text_6R9XD8": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>If you have already been practicing but did not start the session on your device, you can adjust the start time. Press the bottom button and rotate the wheel to set the correct start time.</p><p>When a practice session is active, the <strong>Track</strong> app will automatically open each time you wake the screen for quick access. The LED ring gradually fills with orange to indicate progress toward your goal.</p><p>To disable the orange tracking light, open the mobile app and turn it off in the Core / Spark settings.</p>"
          }
        },
        "image_NyDj7h": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Core_2_Order_13.jpg"
          }
        },
        "text_Wph8pr": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>During an active session, tap the soundwave icon twice quickly to pause or end the session.</p><p>When editing a session, you can delete it or adjust the start and end times.</p>"
          }
        },
        "divider_bc3Uzm": {
          "type": "divider",
          "settings": {}
        },
        "subheading_3gJNCt": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Tracking with our mobile app"
          }
        },
        "text_nT77Fi": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>When you track a practice session on your device or in the mobile app, any changes you make, such as adjusting your goal, instrument, or start time, will automatically sync between both devices. All saved sessions are also synchronized automatically.</p><p>If you experience synchronization issues, you can initiate a manual sync in the mobile app under your device’s settings.</p><p>The mobile app provides several ways to view and analyze your practice data, including a practice calendar, streak tracking, and additional insights.</p>"
          }
        },
        "image_t9EaiU": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Core_2_Order_14.jpg"
          }
        },
        "divider_U7NDz9": {
          "type": "divider",
          "settings": {}
        },
        "heading_3eNxUU": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Vibrating metronome"
          }
        },
        "subheading_zTfCrT": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Body strap"
          }
        },
        "text_3VGXjf": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Where you position the Core / Spark on your body can significantly affect your experience. The optimal placement varies from musician to musician.</p><p>Using the included body strap and body strap rig, you can wear the Core on your wrist, arm, or ankle. With the included extension piece, you can also attach it to your chest, shoulder, or thigh.</p><h4>Tip</h4><p>During your first few sessions, experiment with different positions to determine what feels most comfortable and effective. Wearing the device on your chest typically provides the strongest and most precise vibration feedback.</p><p>Ensure that the strap is secured firmly. A tighter fit enhances the transmission of vibrations and improves the overall experience.</p>"
          }
        },
        "image_chjewp": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Core_2_Order_15_cde650db-62d3-4d7c-a550-eb0337acf687.jpg"
          }
        },
        "text_rgUPrz": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>If you have thin arms or ankles</strong></p><p>To set the body strap to its smallest setting, align the arms of the rig with the markings on the strap as shown in the illustration below.</p>"
          }
        },
        "image_E3Fych": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Core_2_Order_16.jpg"
          }
        },
        "divider_3w6Xgd": {
          "type": "divider",
          "settings": {}
        },
        "subheading_t9TDDQ": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "How to feel the beat"
          }
        },
        "text_3WUEWG": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Using a vibrational metronome is a different experience from using a traditional audible metronome. When you first begin using the Core / Spark, allow yourself time to adapt. Do not be discouraged if it feels unfamiliar at first, as this is a normal part of the learning process.</p><p>With continued use, the vibration can become a subconscious cue that supports your sense of timing and helps you maintain the beat naturally.</p>"
          }
        },
        "divider_fjemp8": {
          "type": "divider",
          "settings": {}
        },
        "subheading_NydDnh": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Setting up a rhythm"
          }
        },
        "text_pitfrD": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>1. Press the bottom button to select the first value.</p><p>2. While selected, use the wheel to change the value.</p>"
          }
        },
        "image_FV98pp": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Core_2_Order_17.jpg"
          }
        },
        "text_9XNnh4": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>3. Press the bottom button again to edit the next value. Press the top button to go back.<br/></p><p>4. Tap the soundwave twice quickly to start or pause the metronome.</p>"
          }
        },
        "image_ViiDii": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Core_2_Order_18_06d82c4b-0518-4e7c-b95a-d1c241c9824e.jpg"
          }
        },
        "text_TqbGXK": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<h4>Tip</h4><p>You can also start the metronome by pressing and holding the bottom button. The metronome will begin as soon as you release the button.</p><p>This method allows you to precisely align the start of the metronome with the rhythm of the music or audio you are listening to.</p>"
          }
        },
        "divider_GzhHqt": {
          "type": "divider",
          "settings": {}
        },
        "subheading_nxFYxr": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Change LED lights, vibrations & sounds"
          }
        },
        "text_PPf9Mq": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Because every musician has different preferences, you can customize your Core / Spark using the mobile app.</p><p><strong>LED lights & vibrations</strong></p><p>To adjust or disable the LED lights and vibrations, open the mobile app and navigate to:</p><p><strong>Settings → Select your Core → Metronome vibrations</strong> or <strong>Metronome lights</strong></p><p>We recommend experimenting with different vibration intensities and durations to find the settings that work best for you.</p><p><strong>Sounds</strong></p><p>To customize or disable the metronome sounds, open the mobile app and go to:</p><p><strong>Settings → App settings → Metronome sounds</strong></p>"
          }
        },
        "image_ppDgRj": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Core_2_Order_19.jpg"
          }
        },
        "divider_kGcVqV": {
          "type": "divider",
          "settings": {}
        },
        "subheading_7pAhzQ": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Multi-player sync"
          }
        },
        "text_fE43Up": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>The Core / Spark can be synchronized with other Soundbrenner wearables by connecting all devices to the same mobile device. You can sync up to five devices simultaneously, allowing everyone to feel the beat together.</p><p>If you would like to connect your Core / Spark to a different mobile device, you must first unpair it from the current device. To access the unpairing prompt, open the <strong>Settings</strong> app on your Core / Spark, navigate to <strong>Bluetooth</strong>, and press the bottom button.</p><p>Once the device is ready to pair, open the Soundbrenner app on the new mobile device. Then navigate to:</p><p><strong>Settings → Add a Soundbrenner wearable</strong></p><p>Select the wearable you would like to connect and follow the on-screen instructions.</p>"
          }
        },
        "image_wWCNAW": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Core_2_Order_20.jpg"
          }
        },
        "divider_XNKXfy": {
          "type": "divider",
          "settings": {}
        },
        "heading_kFjpNR": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Chromatic tuner"
          }
        },
        "subheading_bE3ihU": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Microphone tuner (Core 2 / Spark only)"
          }
        },
        "text_r7gJrb": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Open the <strong>Microphone tuner</strong> app and play a note. The device will detect the closest pitch and display its deviation in cents. As you adjust the pitch, the LED ring will change from red to green to indicate when the note is in tune.</p><p>To adjust the tuning reference (A4), press the bottom button and rotate the wheel to set your preferred frequency (default: 440 Hz).</p>"
          }
        },
        "image_D7bYPy": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Core_2_Order_21.jpg"
          }
        },
        "divider_pgRMDY": {
          "type": "divider",
          "settings": {}
        },
        "subheading_tTkj9B": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Contact tuner"
          }
        },
        "text_hfkATY": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>The original Core includes the <strong>Contact tuner</strong> app pre-installed.</p><p>For Core 2 / Spark, a magnetic tuning accessory is required to use the <strong>Contact tuner</strong> app. You can choose between a tuning clip or adhesive tuning mounts. Each accessory includes a unique code to unlock the Contact Tuner app on Core 2 / Spark.</p><p>Contact tuning is designed for use with guitar, bass guitar, ukulele, and violin.</p><h4>Tip</h4><p>To purchase magnetic tuning accessories, visit:</p>"
          }
        },
        "button_BtwNMt": {
          "type": "button",
          "settings": {
            "label": "Soundbrenner shop",
            "button_size": "large",
            "icon_position": "none",
            "link": "shopify://collections/all"
          }
        },
        "text_awM8te": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>Attaching a magnetic tuner mount</strong></p><p>Each magnetic tuner mount comes with pre-applied adhesive. Remove the protective backing and firmly attach the mount to the headstock of your instrument.</p><p>The tuner mount is designed for long-term use, so you do not need to remove it after each session. If you decide to remove it, peel it off carefully to avoid damaging the surface of your instrument.</p><p><strong>Using the contact tuner</strong></p><ol><li>Open the <strong>Contact tuner</strong> app on your device.</li><li>Remove the wearable from its rig by twisting it counterclockwise.</li><li>Attach the magnetic port on the side of the device to the tuner mount or tuning clip.</li></ol><p>When you play a string, the LED ring and display will activate to show the tuning information.</p>"
          }
        },
        "image_4Q8cPB": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Core_2_Order_22_5f68ba56-6f3a-406a-8b21-c81f076897ed.jpg"
          }
        },
        "divider_UDGGpU": {
          "type": "divider",
          "settings": {}
        },
        "heading_DqMpQN": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Decibel meter"
          }
        },
        "text_BGtakD": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>Sound levels</strong></p><p>Open the <strong>Decibel meter</strong> app to measure current, average, and maximum sound levels. The Core / Spark measures sound levels above 70 dB and uses A-weighting for its readings.</p><h4>Tip (Core only)</h4><p>For improved accuracy, remove the Core from its rig and place it on a soft surface, such as a cloth or your hand, before opening the <strong>Decibel meter</strong> app.</p><p><strong>Volume alarm</strong></p><p>Your Core / Spark monitors sound exposure throughout the day and alerts you when volume levels reach potentially harmful thresholds, based on World Health Organization guidelines:</p><ul><li>80 dB: 5 hours 30 minutes per day</li><li>85 dB: 1 hour 45 minutes per day</li><li>90 dB: 30 minutes per day</li><li>95 dB: 10 minutes per day</li></ul><p>Your privacy is important to us. No audio is recorded or stored at any time.</p><p>To disable the volume alarm and all background sound measurements, open the mobile app and navigate to:</p><p><strong>Settings → Select your device → Volume alarm</strong></p>"
          }
        },
        "image_fbRE9a": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Core_2_Order_23.jpg"
          }
        },
        "divider_NC9YAa": {
          "type": "divider",
          "settings": {}
        },
        "heading_w4TnW9": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Smartwatch"
          }
        },
        "subheading_nPMqjm": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Smartphone notifications"
          }
        },
        "text_U3HEgD": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Smartphone notifications are supported on both iOS and Android devices. Your Core / Spark will mirror the notifications you receive on your mobile device and is compatible with all apps. At this time, it is not possible to enable or disable notifications for individual apps independently from your mobile device settings.</p><p>To receive notifications, iOS and Android require certain permissions. When you connect your device to the Soundbrenner app for the first time, these permissions will be requested automatically during setup.</p><p>If you are not receiving notifications after completing the setup process, please refer to the troubleshooting section below:</p>"
          }
        },
        "accordion_item_f3A3i8": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Core smartphone notifications troubleshooting",
            "answer": "<p>For the device to receive notifications, iOS and Android require specific permissions. When you connect your device to the Soundbrenner app for the first time, these permissions are requested automatically during setup.</p><p>If you are unable to receive notifications after setup, follow the steps below.</p><p><strong>If you are using an iOS device</strong></p><p>Your iPhone must grant the Core / Spark permission to receive notifications.</p><ol><li>Open the <strong>Settings</strong> app on iOS (outside the Soundbrenner app).</li><li>Go to <strong>Bluetooth</strong>.</li><li>Tap the <strong>(i)</strong> icon next to your device.</li><li>Enable <strong>Share System Notifications</strong>.</li></ol><p>If notifications still do not appear, review the <strong>Show Previews</strong> setting:</p><ol><li>Open the <strong>Settings</strong> app on iOS.</li><li>Go to <strong>Notifications → Show Previews</strong>.</li><li>Select <strong>Always</strong> or <strong>When Unlocked</strong>.</li></ol><p>If <strong>Never</strong> is selected, notifications will not be forwarded to your device.</p><p>Note that this setting can also be configured individually per app. To check this:</p><ol><li>Go to <strong>Settings → Notifications</strong>.</li><li>Scroll down and select the relevant app.</li><li>Tap <strong>Show Previews</strong> and ensure it is set to <strong>Always</strong> or <strong>When Unlocked</strong>.</li></ol><p><strong>If you are using an Android device</strong></p><p>First, ensure you have the latest version of the Soundbrenner app installed from Google Play (version 1.23.0 or later). To check, open the app’s page in Google Play and see whether an update is available.</p><p>Next, confirm that the Soundbrenner app has permission to:</p><ol><li>Access your location at all times.</li><li>Access your notifications.</li></ol><p>To verify permissions:</p><ol><li>Open the Soundbrenner app.</li><li>Navigate to <strong>Settings → Select your Core → Smartwatch</strong>.</li></ol><p>If there is no warning displayed below the <strong>Smartphone Notifications</strong> switch, your permissions are correctly configured. If a warning appears, follow the on-screen instructions to grant the required permissions.</p><p><strong>Additional troubleshooting (iOS & Android)</strong></p><ol><li>Ensure your Core is running the latest firmware version (1.5.1 or later). Learn how to update the firmware of your Core <a href=\"https://support.soundbrenner.com/hc/en-us/articles/360037710374\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</li><li>On your Core, open the <strong>Settings</strong> app and confirm that <strong>Smartphone Notifications</strong> is enabled.</li><li>The Core can only receive notifications from the mobile device it was originally unlocked with. This protects your privacy during multi-device sync sessions. If notifications still do not work despite all permissions being enabled, perform a factory reset and set up the device again using the account you are currently logged into.</li><li>If you are still unable to get notifications to work, please reach out to our team at <a href=\"mailto:support@soundbrenner.com\">support@soundbrenner.com</a>. We're looking forward to helping you out. </li></ol>"
          }
        },
        "text_X9Jggx": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>Reading notifications</strong></p><p>New notifications automatically appear on the Core / Spark when you wake the screen.</p>"
          }
        },
        "image_pWEwmn": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Core_2_Order_24.jpg"
          }
        },
        "subheading_7C6VdM": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Manage notifications"
          }
        },
        "text_rAXGi4": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<ul><li>Rotate the wheel to scroll through the text of a notification.</li><li>Press the bottom button to delete the current notification and display the next one in the queue. The number in the top-right corner indicates how many notifications are currently queued.</li><li>Press and hold the bottom button to delete all notifications in the queue.</li><li>Press the top button to send all queued notifications to the Notification Center (up to a maximum of 20).</li><li>To access the Notification Center, rotate the wheel to the right while on the watch face.</li></ul>"
          }
        },
        "image_JwgLWG": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Core_2_Order_25.jpg"
          }
        },
        "text_nVhP36": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>Phone calls</strong></p><p>When you receive a phone call, the Core / Spark will vibrate and display the option to accept or decline the call.</p><p>As the Core / Spark does not have a built-in speaker or microphone, you will need to use your phone or connected Bluetooth headphones to conduct the call.</p>"
          }
        },
        "divider_BmnLkM": {
          "type": "divider",
          "settings": {}
        },
        "subheading_zztz43": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Smartphone music remote (Core 2 / Spark only)"
          }
        },
        "text_XgaEYF": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Control any media playing on your mobile device, including music, videos, podcasts, and audiobooks. This feature is compatible with all apps, such as Apple Music, Spotify, and YouTube.</p><p>On Android devices, the Soundbrenner app requires access to your notifications to enable this feature.</p><p>1. Rotate the wheel to the left to access the <strong>Smartphone music remote</strong>.</p><p>2. Tap the soundwave icon twice quickly to start or pause playback.</p><p></p>"
          }
        },
        "image_iEpim6": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Core_2_Order_26_703c7e0f-16c0-4c43-889c-f2c711c1f354.jpg"
          }
        },
        "text_p6RUM9": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>3. Press the bottom button to select the current media playing. Twist the wheel forward for next, backward for previous.</p><p>4. Press the bottom button again to select the volume. Twist the wheel forward to increase, backward to decrease.</p>"
          }
        },
        "image_ctxrVb": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Core_2_Order_27_dd1a31de-13a4-4584-a847-b8f8d38fe4c9.jpg"
          }
        },
        "divider_yGiD6W": {
          "type": "divider",
          "settings": {}
        },
        "subheading_qcM8GX": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Timer"
          }
        },
        "text_8awQtz": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Press the bottom button to select whether you want to adjust the hours, minutes, or seconds. Once selected, rotate the wheel to set the desired time.</p><p>Tap the soundwave icon twice quickly to start or pause the timer.</p>"
          }
        },
        "subheading_wqcpNK": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Stopwatch"
          }
        },
        "text_rfGpyy": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Tap the soundwave twice quickly to start or pause the stopwatch.</p>"
          }
        },
        "subheading_3rT9jG": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Alarm"
          }
        },
        "text_hdLRXH": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>To create an alarm, rotate the wheel to select <strong>New alarm</strong>, then press the bottom button to confirm.</p><p>Use the wheel to set the desired time. Press the bottom button to select the days on which the alarm should be active. Rotate the wheel to the right to enable a specific day. Active days are indicated by an underline. If no days are underlined, the alarm is active every day by default.</p><p>To change the alarm status, select <strong>On</strong> using the bottom button. Rotate the wheel to choose <strong>Off</strong> or <strong>Delete</strong>, then press the bottom button to confirm your selection.</p>"
          }
        },
        "subheading_8T3AUg": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Settings"
          }
        },
        "text_DcDGni": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p><strong>Airplane mode</strong></p><p>Disables all wireless communication, including Bluetooth. When Airplane Mode is enabled, the device cannot connect to your mobile device.</p><p><strong>Bluetooth</strong></p><p>Displays the current connection status. Press the bottom button to unpair the device and make it available for pairing again.</p><p><strong>Factory reset</strong></p><p>Erases all data and preferences and restores the Core / Spark to its factory settings. After a factory reset, the device will be locked until setup is completed again using the Soundbrenner app.</p>"
          }
        },
        "divider_G4W7PG": {
          "type": "divider",
          "settings": {}
        },
        "heading_8JzcNh": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Troubleshooting"
          }
        },
        "subheading_LiwjxQ": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Connecting to your mobile device"
          }
        },
        "text_bR3bMT": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>If you are having problems to connect your Core, Core 2 or Spark to your mobile device, try the steps below to resolve your problem.</p>"
          }
        },
        "accordion_item_97qzHE": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "If you have an Android device",
            "answer": "<p>Note that due to the many different Android versions, some of the system menu items described below may have different names for you. Some permissions may also not exist altogether in your Android version.</p><ul><li><strong>Powered up:</strong> Make sure your wearable is powered on and not out of battery. If you're new and you're not sure, check out our \"Getting started\" how-to video <a href=\"https://support.soundbrenner.com/hc/en-us/articles/900001243703\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</li><li><strong>Pair in Soundbrenner app:</strong> You need to pair the wearable from within the Soundbrenner app. Do not pair it from the Bluetooth settings of your mobile device. After installing the Soundbrenner app, simply follow its onboarding instructions. If the app was already installed before, go to \"Settings\" in the bottom navigation menu of our app → \"Add a Soundbrenner wearable\".</li><li><strong>Unpair on your wearable:</strong> This is to make sure your wearable is not paired to anything and available for pairing. Open the \"Settings\" app on your wearable. Navigate to \"Bluetooth\" and press the bottom button twice to confirm. This will remove any prior pairing and make your wearable available for pairing again. </li><li><strong>Unpair on mobile device:</strong> If you paired your wearable to your mobile device before, sometimes it can help to remove it and start from scratch. To do so, navigate to \"Settings\" in the bottom navigation menu of our mobile app. If you can see your wearable here, tap on the small three dots on the right side next to it. Select \"Remove\". Next go to Android settings (outside the Soundbrenner app) and tap on \"Connected devices\". Find your wearable and tap on the gear icon. Select \"Forget\" and \"Forget device\". Now come back to the Soundbrenner app and try connecting your wearable again and see if it resolved your problem.</li><li><strong>Turn on required features:</strong> Make sure your Android device's \"Bluetooth\" is turned on and \"Location services\" are also turned on. You can turn on Bluetooth via Android settings (outside the Soundbrenner app) → \"Connected devices\" → \"Connection preferences\" → \"Bluetooth\" → \"Use Bluetooth\". You can turn on Location services via Android settings (outside the Soundbrenner app) → \"Location\" → \"Use location\".</li><li><strong>Grant required permissions:</strong> Android requires our app to receive several permissions from you before it allows our app to connect a wearable. Our app should ask for all of them automatically if it detects they are missing, but you can verify everything is in order via the steps below:Location permission: Go to Android settings (outside the Soundbrenner app) → \"Apps\" → \"Soundbrenner\" → \"Permissions\" → \"Location\". If \"Allow all the time\" is available as an option, you must select it. If \"Allow all the time\" is not available, select \"Allow only while using the app\". To improve the chances the Bluetooth connection will work reliably, try enabling \"Use precise location\".Bluetooth permission: Go to Android settings (outside the Soundbrenner app) → \"Apps\" → \"Soundbrenner\" → \"Permissions\" → \"Nearby devices\" → \"Allow\".</li><li><strong>Disable battery optimization:</strong> Android's battery optimization can sometimes get in the way of a reliable Bluetooth connection. Go to Android settings (outside the Soundbrenner app) → \"Apps\" → \"Soundbrenner\" → \"Battery\" → Select \"Unrestricted\"</li><li><strong>Compatibility: </strong>Visit <a href=\"https://support.soundbrenner.com/hc/en-us/articles/www.soundbrenner.com/compatibility\" target=\"_blank\">www.soundbrenner.com/compatibility</a> to check if you have an incompatible mobile device.</li><li><strong>Remove other Bluetooth devices:</strong> On some Android mobile devices it can cause issues if you have too many Bluetooth devices connected at the same time. If you are experiencing issues, remove other devices via Android settings (outside the Soundbrenner app) → \"Connected devices\" → Gear icon → \"Forget\" → \"Forget device\"</li><li><strong>Restart mobile device:</strong> Try turning off your mobile device and restarting it. Sometimes this can solve the problem.</li><li><strong>Contact support:</strong> If you are still having problems, please reach out to us.</li></ul>"
          }
        },
        "accordion_item_fmV7jz": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "If you have an iOS device",
            "answer": "<ul><li><strong>Powered up:</strong> Make sure your wearable is powered on and not out of battery. If you're new and you're not sure, check out our \"Getting started\" how-to video <a href=\"https://support.soundbrenner.com/hc/en-us/articles/900001243703\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.</li><li><strong>Pair in Soundbrenner app:</strong> You need to pair the wearable from within the Soundbrenner app. Do not pair it from the Bluetooth settings of your mobile device. After installing the Soundbrenner app, simply follow its onboarding instructions. If the app was already installed before, go to \"Settings\" in the bottom navigation menu of our app → \"Add a Soundbrenner wearable\".</li><li><strong>Unpair on your wearable:</strong> This is to make sure your wearable is not paired to anything and available for pairing. Open the \"Settings\" app on your wearable. Navigate to \"Bluetooth\" and press the bottom button twice to confirm. This will remove any prior pairing and make your wearable available for pairing again. </li><li><strong>Unpair on mobile device:</strong> If you paired your wearable to your mobile device before, sometimes it can help to remove it and start from scratch. To do so, navigate to \"Settings\" in the bottom navigation menu of our mobile app. If you can see your wearable here, swipe from right to left. Tap the \"Remove\" button that appears. Next go to iOS settings (outside the Soundbrenner app) → Bluetooth → Tap on (i) next to your wearable → Tap on \"Forget This Device\" and \"Forget Device\". Now come back to the Soundbrenner app and try connecting again and you will successfully pair and connect your wearable.</li><li><strong>Compatibility: </strong>Visit <a href=\"https://support.soundbrenner.com/hc/en-us/articles/www.soundbrenner.com/compatibility\" target=\"_blank\">www.soundbrenner.com/compatibility</a> to check if you have an incompatible mobile device.</li><li><strong>Restart mobile device:</strong> Try turning off your mobile device and restarting it. Sometimes this can solve the problem.</li><li><strong>Contact support:</strong> If you are still having problems, please reach out to us.</li></ul>"
          }
        },
        "subheading_qTRhUi": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Soft restart"
          }
        },
        "text_6mCaUq": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>If your device behaves unexpectedly, press and hold both buttons for 5 seconds, and continue holding them until Recovery Mode appears.</p><p>Use the bottom button to select <strong>Restart</strong> and perform a soft restart.</p><p>If the device remains unresponsive, perform a hard restart.</p>"
          }
        },
        "image_L8yyXG": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Core_2_Order_28_774d1249-6672-45a8-a36f-916890b9c4cf.jpg"
          }
        },
        "subheading_D9MaqY": {
          "type": "subheading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Hard restart"
          }
        },
        "text_nGgRmi": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>This procedure should only be used if your Core / Spark is unresponsive.</p><p>Ensure that the charging cable is connected to a power source. Attach the cable to the magnetic port on the device, then detach it. Immediately reattach the cable a second time to initiate the hard restart.</p>"
          }
        },
        "image_7Wy3B7": {
          "type": "image",
          "settings": {
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/Product_Core_2_Order_2.jpg"
          }
        },
        "divider_89iXCF": {
          "type": "divider",
