        "heading_jbn8mk": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Compliance"
          }
        },
        "accordion_item_YML4rP": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Safety",
            "answer": "<p>Warning: medical conditions</p><p>If you currently have a medical condition or have a history of medical conditions that may be affected by the Soundbrenner Core/Spark, consult with your physician before using the product. Medical conditions include (but are not limited to):</p><ul><li>White Knuckle Syndrome</li><li>Hand-Arm Vibration Syndrome</li><li>Blackouts</li><li>Epilepsy</li><li>Postural Hypertension</li><li>Allergic Reactions to Silicone</li><li>Any other heart, neurological, or skin conditions</li></ul><p>Warning: medical device interference</p><p>If you use any medical device that may be affected by the Soundbrenner Core/Spark, consult with your physician before using the product. Medical devices include (but are not limited to):</p><ul><li>Coronary Stents</li><li>Defibrillators</li><li>Pacemakers</li><li>Any other implanted medical device</li></ul><p>Stop using the Soundbrenner Core/Spark if you suspect that it is interfering with your medical device or if you experience any discomfort.</p><p>Warning: frequent and prolonged usage</p><p>Frequent and prolonged use of the Soundbrenner Core/Spark may cause skin irritation in some users. If you experience itchiness, redness, and/or swelling while using the Soundbrenner Core/Spark, remove the device immediately and stop using it until your skin returns to normal. Consult your doctor should any of the symptoms persist.</p><p>Caution: electrical equipment</p><p>Your Soundbrenner Core/Spark and its charging cable are electrical devices and should be handled with care. Never use your device in extremely low or high temperatures.</p><p>Substances in this product and battery may harm the environment or cause injury if handled or disposed of improperly.</p><p>Remove your Soundbrenner Core/Spark if it feels warm or hot.</p><p>Caution: magnets</p><p>The Soundbrenner Core/Spark and the charging cable contain magnets. All credit cards, key cards, and any other object containing a magnetic stripe should be stowed safely away from those products.</p><p>Caution: batteries</p><p>Use only an authorized Soundbrenner charging cable to charge your device to avoid any safety or electrical hazards.</p><p>Do not attempt to change the battery on your own. This will void the warranty and could cause injury.</p><p>Always disconnect the charging cable from the electrical socket as soon as your device is fully charged.</p><p>Never charge your device when moisture is present.</p><p>Never put your device or charging cable near any inflammable or explosive materials.</p><p>Caution: water</p><p>Even though your Soundbrenner Core/Spark is sweat proof and partially water-resistant, it should never be submerged in water under any circumstances.</p><p>Do not use your device in the rain or in wet environments for prolonged periods.</p>"
          }
        },
